e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoney-market%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaped%20as%20high%20as%205%25%2C%20giving%20investors%20attractive%20risk-free%20returns%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-new-economic-supercycle-growth-inflation-stock-market-global-chaos-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeopolitical%20upheaval%20means%20the%20world%3C%2Fa%3E%20feels%20extremely%20shaky%3B%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-fears-fueling-stock-market-crash-wall-street-chaos-positive-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20pros%20have%20been%20warning%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-recession-stock-market-crash-calls-wrong-economy-housing-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recession%20for%20over%20a%20year%20now%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20younger%20investors%2C%20I%20think%20the%20scars%20run%20deeper%20than%20worries%20about%20a%20coming%20downturn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EMillennials%20have%20had%20a%20tumultuous%20induction%20into%20adulthood.%20Many%20of%20them%20were%20in%20high%20school%20or%20college%20or%20in%20their%20early%20working%20years%20during%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis.%20From%202009%20to%202014%2C%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20was%2010%25%20or%20higher%20for%2020-%20to%2024-year-old%20Americans.%20They%20learned%20to%20prioritize%20cash%20as%20they%20navigated%20one%20of%20the%20worst%20downturns%20in%20history.%20Then%2C%20just%20as%20they%20were%20finding%20their%20footing%2C%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20hit.%20We%20were%20locked%20inside%20our%20houses%20for%20weeks%20on%20end%20while%20stocks%20entered%20one%20of%20their%20swiftest%20crashes%20on%20record.%20Soon%20after%2C%20we%20nervously%20waded%20back%20into%20the%20wealth-building%20waters%2C%20only%20to%20get%20hit%20by%20scorching%20inflation%20and%20another%20bear%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FPWfeo%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Millennial%20cash%20holdings%20and%20recessions%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22469%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20generation%20has%20its%20war%20stories.%20Gen%20Xers%20had%20to%20process%209%2F11%20and%20the%20tech%20bubble%20bursting%20in%20their%20late%2020s.%20Baby%20boomers%20dealt%20with%20their%20own%20bout%20of%20inflation%20and%20high%20rates%20as%2020-year-olds%20in%20the%201980s.%20Their%20parents%20were%20unfortunate%20enough%20to%20experience%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20a%20three-year%20stretch%20of%20the%20darkest%20economic%20days%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20But%20there's%20something%20especially%20pernicious%20about%20having%20to%20navigate%20not%20one%20but%20two%20earth-shattering%20crises%20early%20in%20adulthood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoney%20can%20be%20a%20highly%20personal%20subject.%20Our%20feelings%20of%20financial%20stability%20develop%20through%20experiences%2C%20not%20classes%20or%20textbooks.%20A%202017%20University%20of%20Michigan%20study%20found%20that%20children%20as%20young%20as%205%20could%20start%20developing%20spending%20and%20saving%20habits.%20There's%20also%20a%20ton%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-people-are-developing-money-dysmorphia-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%20that%20suggests%20financial%20stress%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20lead%20to%20a%20litany%20of%20physical%2C%20mental%2C%20and%20emotional%20issues.%20Early%20financial%20trauma%20can%20profoundly%20shape%20your%20relationship%20with%20money.%20That's%20why%20personal%20finance%20can%20feel%20so%20illogical%20at%20times%20%E2%80%94%20why%20some%20of%20us%20may%20be%20set%20on%20paper%20but%20constantly%20fear%20losing%20it%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20this%20well.%20I'm%20a%20young%20millennial%20who%20felt%20the%20financial%20crisis%20as%20a%20teenager.%20My%20mom%20was%20a%20part-time%20bookkeeper%20at%20a%20housing%20construction%20company%2C%20and%20my%20dad%20was%20a%20residential%20electrician.%20You%20could%20probably%20guess%20what%20happened%20when%20the%20housing%20market%20went%20into%20a%20tailspin.%20I%20may%20not%20have%20been%20old%20enough%20to%20open%20a%20brokerage%20account%2C%20but%20I%20picked%20up%20some%20perverse%20money%20habits%20from%20the%20financial%20crisis%20that%20I'm%20trying%20to%20unlearn%20%E2%80%94%20even%20now%2C%20as%20the%20head%20of%20research%20at%20a%20firm%20that%20teaches%20people%20how%20to%20build%20wealth.%20Multiply%20this%20mentality%20across%20a%20generation%2C%20and%20you%20have%20one%20swath%20who%20brought%20us%20crypto%2C%20Occupy%20Wall%20Street%2C%20meme%20stocks%2C%20and%20YOLO%20capitalism%2C%20and%20another%20batch%20that%20can't%20seem%20to%20take%20enough%20risks%20to%20build%20a%20decent%20retirement%20fund.%20These%20more%20cautious%20ones%20piled%20their%20savings%20into%20inflation-linked%20I-bonds%20%E2%80%94%20super-safe%20government-issued%20debt%20that%20locks%20away%20your%20money%20for%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20when%20they%20hit%209%25%20in%202022.%20A%20great%20decision%20for%20an%20emergency%20fund%2C%20but%20less%20savvy%20when%20the%20stock%20market%20is%20plumbing%20new%20lows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaving%20too%20much%20money%20seems%20like%20a%20good%20problem%20to%20have%2C%20but%20keeping%20all%20your%20money%20in%20a%20savings%20account%20can%20be%20a%20huge%20financial%20mistake%20when%20you%20consider%20the%20opportunity%20cost.%20Imagine%20you%20put%20%241%2C000%20in%20a%20savings%20account%20in%20July%202023%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20Fed's%20rate%20hikes%20%E2%80%94%20earning%20a%20sweet%205%25%20APY%20on%20your%20cash.%20By%20October%204%2C%20you%20would've%20earned%20about%20%2460%20on%20that%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20does%20that%20compare%20to%20stock-market%20returns%3F%20Not%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20staying%20in%20cash%20over%20the%20past%20year%20and%20change%2C%20you%20missed%20a%2027%25%20rally%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20that%20%241%2C000%20would've%20turned%20into%20about%20%241%2C277%20if%20you'd%20invested%20it%20in%20a%20no-fee%20index%20fund.%20There%20were%20strong%20gains%20to%20be%20had%20in%20other%20major%20indexes%2C%20too%3A%20a%2028%25%20climb%20in%20the%20tech-heavy%20Nasdaq%20100%20and%20an%2018%25%20rise%20in%20the%20mega-company%20Dow.%20Yes%2C%20even%20your%20grandma's%20index%20beat%20your%20cash%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20stocks%20and%20cash%20are%20different%20financial%20beasts.%20Cash%20can%20be%20dependable%20in%20tough%20times%2C%20and%20it's%20often%20the%20best%20place%20to%20stash%20away%20funds%20for%20a%20big%20purchase.%20It%20also%20makes%20sense%20to%20have%20some%20cash%20on%20hand.%20Stocks%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20are%20often%20far%20from%20stable.%20Lots%20of%20popular%20stocks%20have%20dropped%2010%25%20to%2020%25%20of%20their%20value%20in%20a%20single%20day%2C%20and%20you%20could%20theoretically%20lose%20all%20your%20invested%20money%20in%20the%20stock%20market.%20But%20as%20scary%20as%20that%20sounds%2C%20it's%20the%20essence%20of%20risk-taking%3B%20you%20give%20up%20stability%20for%20potentially%20greater%20returns%20over%20time.%20If%20you%20have%20decades%20ahead%20of%20you%20as%20an%20investor%2C%20you're%20in%20a%20prime%20spot%20to%20take%20some%20risks.%20Every%20little%20bit%20matters%2C%20too.%20Over%20long%20periods%2C%20the%20difference%20between%205%25%20and%206%25%20returns%20on%20a%20%241%2C000%20investment%20can%20be%20thousands%20of%20dollars.%20For%20what%20it's%20worth%2C%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20%E2%80%94%20an%20index%20of%20America's%20largest%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20has%20grown%20by%20about%208%25%20a%20year%20over%20th