e%20has%20been%20wiped%20from%20WiseTech%20Global%20Ltd.%20this%20week%20after%20media%20reports%20that%20White%20-%20the%20company's%20co-founder%2C%20chief%20executive%20officer%20and%20largest%20shareholder%20-%20paid%20millions%20of%20dollars%20to%20a%20former%20sexual%20partner%20to%20settle%20allegations%20of%20inappropriate%20behavior.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20board%20review%20underway%2C%20the%20crisis%20enveloping%20the%20freight%20software%20giant%20and%20its%20figurehead%20CEO%20deepened%20Thursday%20as%20the%20Australian%20Financial%20Review%20reported%20a%20former%20director%20had%20accused%20White%20of%20intimidation%20and%20bullying.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20newspaper%20said%20White%20also%20had%20a%20years-long%20relationship%20with%20an%20employee%20before%20gifting%20her%20a%20A%247%20million%20waterfront%20house%20in%20Melbourne.%20The%20transaction%20wasn't%20disclosed%20to%20the%20board%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHelen%20Karlis%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20White's%20lawyers%20at%20Clayton%20Utz%2C%20said%20the%20law%20firm%20had%20no%20immediate%20comment%20on%20the%20latest%20allegations%20that%20have%20been%20aired.%20The%20firm%20hasn't%20responded%20to%20earlier%20repeated%20requests%20for%20comment.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20matter%20of%20months%2C%20accusations%20of%20operational%20or%20ethical%20failures%20have%20also%20hit%20Australia's%20two%20dominant%20supermarkets%2C%20one%20of%20the%20major%20banks%2C%20the%20largest%20insurer%2C%20the%20biggest%20listed%20media%20company%20and%20Sydney's%20main%20casino.%20In%20a%20country%20with%20one%20of%20the%20planet's%20biggest%20pension%20pools%2C%20where%20worker%20contributions%20are%20mandatory%2C%20everyday%20savers%20are%20picking%20up%20the%20tab%20when%20stock%20prices%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20tycoon%20founder%2C%20Mineral%20Resources%20Ltd.'s%20Chris%20Ellison%2C%20also%20this%20week%20found%20himself%20embroiled%20in%20scandal%20with%20the%20company%20investigating%20historic%20undeclared%20payments%20that%20helped%20him%20avoid%20tax.%20Australia's%20corporate%20watchdog%20has%20launched%20a%20probe%2C%20and%20almost%20A%242%20billion%20has%20been%20slashed%20from%20the%20miner's%20market%20value%20since%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mining%20magnate%20described%20his%20actions%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Monday%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20poor%20decision%20and%20a%20serious%20lapse%20of%20judgment.%26quot%3B%20He%20had%20subsequently%20%26quot%3Bvoluntarily%26quot%3B%20disclosed%20the%20matters%20to%20the%20Australian%20Taxation%20Office%20in%20full%2C%20with%20all%20outstanding%20tax%2C%20penalties%20and%20interest%20repaid.%20The%20company's%20board%20said%20earlier%20this%20week%20it%20retained%20confidence%20in%20Ellison.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20executive%20or%20corporate%20transgressions%20are%20a%20worldwide%20phenomenon%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20be%20particularly%20pronounced%20in%20Australia%2C%20where%20a%20confluence%20of%20factors%20come%20into%20play.%20Many%20of%20the%20country's%20largest%20industries%20-%20aviation%2C%20banking%2C%20groceries%20and%20retailing%20-%20are%20duopolies%20or%20oligopolies%2C%20comfortable%20environments%20that%20can%20be%20conducive%20for%20market-power%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAustralia%20is%20home%20to%20only%2027%20million%20people%20and%20has%20a%20relatively%20small%20pool%20of%20independent%20board%20directors%20to%20oversee%20listed%20companies.%20Many%20directors%20have%20roles%20at%20multiple%20businesses.%20Advocacy%20groups%20have%20long%20said%20board%20members%20are%20reluctant%20to%20speak%20out%20when%20standards%20lapse%20at%20one%20company%20for%20fear%20of%20losing%20a%20board%20position%20at%20another%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20the%20only%20problem.%20Some%20of%20the%20country's%20watchdogs%20are%20either%20short%20of%20resources%2C%20have%20few%20corporate%20scalps%20to%20their%20name%2C%20or%20dish%20out%20fines%20that%20do%20little%20to%20deter%20bad%20behavior.%20Star%20Entertainment%20Group%20Ltd.%20was%20this%20month%20fined%20just%20A%2415%20million%20-%20less%20than%201%25%20of%20revenue%20-%20by%20its%20regulator%20after%20an%20inquiry%20found%20the%20casino%20operator%20had%20breached%20its%20license%20several%20times%20and%20was%20unfit%20to%20run%20its%20flagship%20Sydney%20complex%2C%20despite%20having%20had%20two%20years%20to%20address%20its%20problems.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20of%20a%20Senate%20inquiry%20into%20the%20Australian%20Securities%20and%20Investments%20Commission%2C%20the%20country's%20primary%20corporate%20regulator%2C%20in%20July%20described%20the%20agency%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20organization%20without%20transparency%2C%20few%20prosecutions%2C%20and%20a%20litany%20of%20cultural%2C%20structural%20and%20governance%20issues.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20damning%20assessments%20of%20an%20Australian%20workplace%20came%20only%20last%20week%20when%20Nine%20Entertainment%20Co.%2C%20publisher%20of%20the%20Sydney%20Morning%20Herald%20and%20the%20AFR%2C%20released%20an%20independent%20review%20of%20its%20own%20practices.%20The%20report%20uncovered%20systemic%20abuses%20of%20power%20and%20authority%2C%20bullying%2C%20discrimination%20and%20sexual%20harassment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20too%20many%20businesses%2C%20internal%20governance%20measures%20aren't%20detecting%20problems%20before%20they%20develop%20into%20major%20public%20scandals%2C%20said%20Rahat%20Munir%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Macquarie%20University's%20business%20school%20who%20leads%20the%20department%20of%20accounting%20and%20corporate%20governance.%20Australia's%20geographical%20remoteness%2C%20far%20from%20the%20world's%20major%20financial%20and%20corporate%20hubs%2C%20means%20its%20companies%20risk%20operating%20in%20their%20own%20bubble%2C%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%2C%20it's%20very%2C%20very%20easy%20to%20manipulate%20the%20local%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWiseTech%20Woes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20WiseTech%2C%20shareholders%20feeling%20the%20pain%20from%20the%20claims%20against%20White%20and%20the%20board%20include%20Australia's%20sovereign%20wealth%20fund%2C%20along%20with%20its%20largest%20pension%20fund%2C%20AustralianSuper%20Pty.%20WiseTech%20shares%20fell%20as%20much%20as%205.8%25%20Thursday%2C%20with%20the%20stock%20on%20track%20for%20its%20worst%20monthly%20performance%20since%20February%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20should%20all%20be%20concerned%20that%20these%20are%20not%20isolated%20examples%2C%20but%20a%20pattern%20of%20behavior%20that%20is%20causing%20direct%20losses%20to%20shareholders%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Brendan%20Lyon%2C%20a%20professor%20with%20the%20University%20of%20Wollongong's%20faculty%20of%20business%20and%20law.%20Corporate%20regulation%20is%20failing%2C%20Lyon%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20flurry%20of%20allegations%20against%20WiseTech%20and%20White%20now%20threaten%20the%20company's%20leadership.%20Former%20director%20Christine%20Holman%20accused%20White%20of%20%26quot%3Bsustained%20intimidation%20and%20bullying%26quot%3B%20as%20she%20quit%20the%20board%20in%20October%202019%20after%20less%20than%20a%20year%2C%20the%20AFR%20reported%20Thursday.%20The%20AFR%20said%20it%20wasn't%20suggesting%20White%20bullied%20or%20intimidated%20Holman%2C%20only%20that%20she%20accused%20him%20of%20doing%20so.%20Holman%20declined%20to%20comment%20to%20the%20newspaper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAGL%20Energy%20Ltd.%2C%20where%20Holman%20is%20now%20a%20board%20member%2C%20forwarded%20her%20an%20interview%20request%20from%20Bloomberg%20News%20earlier%20this%20week%2C%20which%20she%20declined.%20AGL%20didn't%20reply%20to%20a%20fresh%20request%20from%20Bloomberg%20on%20Thursday%20for%20comment%20from%20Holman%20on%20her%20reported%20resignation%20letter%20from%20WiseTech.%3C%2