d%20for%20Nature%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERinchen%20Wangchuk%2C%20Dr%20Tsewang%20Namgail%2C%20and%20Jigmet%20Dadul%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20late%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk%20%E2%80%94%20a%20wildlife%20researcher%20from%20Ladakh%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F246169%2Fladakh-snow-leopard-conservancy-india-trust-saviours-rinchen-wangchuk-tsewang-namgail-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESnow%20Leopard%20Conservancy-India%20Trust%3C%2Fa%3E%20(SLC-IT)%20%E2%80%94%20and%20his%20successor%20(current%20director%20of%20SLC-IT)%20Dr%20Tsewang%20Namgail%2C%20understood%20very%20early%20on%20the%20need%20to%20reconcile%20snow%20leopard%20conservation%20with%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20local%20communities%20who%20lose%20their%20livestock%2C%20particularly%20sheep%20and%20goats%2C%20to%20these%20elusive%20wild%20cats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20growing%20up%20as%20a%20child%20herder%20in%20the%20picturesque%20Skurbuchan%20village%20in%20Leh%20district%2C%20Dr%20Namgail%20understood%20what%20it%20meant%20for%20local%20communities%20to%20lose%20their%20goats%20and%20sheep%20to%20snow%20leopards.%20This%20is%20something%20even%20the%20late%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk%20and%20Jigmet%20Dadul%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20leading%20Snow%20Leopard%20naturalists%20and%20trackers%20%E2%80%94%20also%20understood%20as%20they%20spent%20entire%20winters%20living%20in%20tents%20and%20monitoring%20snow%20leopards%20in%20the%201990s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F12%2FRinchen-Wangchuk-500x735.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Late%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F